Transcription.Text: The two admirals were ad odds with one # another. The commissioners in charge of supplies, when asked for a few nails, refused to issue less than a ton. Half-starved and unprotected against the Russian winter, our troops died in their thousands: lack of fodder killed the horses and mules; there was no other transport.
